@Node "INCLUDEFILE" "ME_English.guide/INHALT/INCLUDEFILE"
@Next "IMAGESETS"
@Toc "INHALT"

The include file
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
    The include file defines some useful new  MUI-macros for shorter and
nicer source code:
  
  - New gadget types: ...UInteger(), ...SInteger(), ...Note(),
    KeyPopupButton(), ...ToggleButton()
 
  - New label type ...CLabel...() for centered labels
 
  - New spacing macros: HBar, VBar, HBarFixed(), VBarFixed()
 
  - "Wt"-version for some gadget macros (additional weight-argument)

    If you want to use the Intege-  or Note-macros  of the include file,
you must insert the following lines before the first macro call.

    TEXT acceptSNumbers[] = ACCEPTSNUMBERS; /* For ...SInteger() */
    TEXT acceptUNumbers[] = ACCEPTUNUMBERS; /* For ...UInteger() */
    TEXT acceptNotes[] = ACCEPTNOTES;       /* For     ...Note() */

    I haven't  inserted the lines  in the include  file because then you
couldn't include it into GST files (with SAS/C compiler) for example.


@EndNode

@Node "IMAGESETS" "ME_English.guide/INHALT/IMAGESETS"
@Next "ICONS"
@Prev "INCLUDEFILE"
@Toc "INHALT"

The MUI-image sets
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
    The package contains 6 MUI-Image-Sets:
  
  - Jojo_Black_11pt

  - Jojo_Black_13pt

  - Jojo_3D_11pt

  - Jojo_3D_13pt

  - Jojo_Outline_11pt

  - Jojo_Outline_13pt

    The image sets should be used with a 11- or 13-pixel font.
    The image set  `Jojo_Black_11pt'  beinhaltet  images for arrows, all
kinds of Popup objects,  Checkmarks,  RadioButtons,  Cycle gadgets,  the
Assign symbol,  the Network symbol and  the TapePause symbol.  The other
images were overtaken from the XEN-Sets.  So you can delete the XEN-sets
completly from your harddisk if you want to have place.
    The other sets contain  only the images which  are diffenrent to the
images in `Jojo_Black_11pt'.
    Except of the TapePause-,  Assign-  and Network-images,   all images
look   like the XEN-buttons.   The TapePause-image  contains  simply two
vertical bars instead of one   (I looked at every tape- and CD-player in
the house and saw that everywhere is a  `||' and not a `|' on the pause-
buttons).
    If you want my  images to look best,   do the following  (If you use
MagicWB, the first 3 points should already be done):

  - Use a screen  with at least  8  colors and a  width  similar  to the
    height (640 x 512 for example).

  - Use the MagicWB palette (or something similar).

  - Use a 11 or a 13 pixel font for Screen text.

  - Start the MUI prefs program.

  - Chose `XEN Lo' or `XEN Hi' from the `Edit/Presets' menu.

  - Change  the images  to the images  in  Jojo_Black..,   Jojo_3D..  or
    Jojo_Outline.. (page Images).

  - If you don't  have MagicWB change  the font names from  `XHelvetica'
    to `helvetica' (page Fonts).

    Additionally there is a  so-called MUI image construction set in the
package: an ILBM picture with the iamges of all sets on it.  You can use
this picture file as model for your own images.

@EndNode

