The icons
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
    I tried to let the icons to  look like like the icons in the MagicWB
package. I must say that *my* icons don't look as good as `real' MagicWB
icons, but maybe Martin Huttenloher sees my icons and draws better ones.

    The  package also  contains a ILBM file with  some new  and old icon
templates.

@EndNode

@Node "FARBPALETTEN" "ME_English.guide/INHALT/FARBPALETTEN"
@Next "PATTERNS"
@Prev "ICONS"
@Toc "INHALT"

The color palettes
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
    The  color  palettes shall be  alternatives to the  orginal  MagicWB
palette.   Every palette exists as ILBM file  (OS 3.0 or better)  and as
`pre'  file  (OS 2.x).    But  you  needn't  to  know that  because  the
installation will install the right palettes.
    The palettes  `OriginalPalette.ilbm' and  `OriginalPalette.pre'  are
the original MagicWB palettes.

@EndNode

@Node "PATTERNS" "ME_English.guide/INHALT/PATTERNS"
@Next "FONTS"
@Prev "FARBPALETTEN"
@Toc "INHALT"

The background patterns
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
    In  the package  there are  a few  new background  patterns  in ILBM
format.  The patterns use the original MagicWB palette,  so OS 2.0 users
can use them at once with NickPrefs.

    There  are  background  patterns  for  the  Workbench windows  under
OS 2.x, too. They have the format for the prefs editor `WBPattern'.

@EndNode

@Node "FONTS" "ME_English/INHALT/FONTS"
@Next "MOUSEPOINTER"
@Prev "PATTERNS"
@Toc "INHALT"

Fonts
¯¯¯¯¯
    In this  version are 4 new  color fonts included  -  but only in the
full version of registered users.     Unregistered users can display the
ILBM  picture file  `MEFonts.ilbm',   on which are a  few chars of every
font.

    The color fonts are ideal  for your own icon projects,  because they
use the original MagicWB color palette.   The following fonts are in the
package:

    - Helvetica/23
    - HelveticaPlain/23
    - Times/21
    - TimesPlain21

    The fonts don't exist as normal color fonts but every char exists as
a single  IFF/ILBM  brush.  The reason for that is that I didn't know  a
program to create color fonts  but a shareware program, which I found so
bad that I didn't want to pay the shareware fee (In the non-full-version
you wasn't able to save).   If someone knows a good program, it would be
nice to tell me  its name or to send it to me.   Otherwise I maybe write
such a program myself - certainly with MUI interface :)

@EndNode

@Node "MOUSEPOINTER" "ME_English/INHALT/MOUSEPOINTER"
@Prev "FONTS"
@Toc "INHALT"

Mouse pointers
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
    Another new thing in  this version are the mouse pointers.    I drew
them for OS 2.x users  (LoRes resultion, max. width 16 pixel).  They use
4 or 8 colors,  at least one of them is a  grey which is  used for anti-
aliasing  (With such a low resultion you must have anti-aliasing). There
are normal mouse pointers in the package, busy pointers and busy pointer
animations   (The last two are for the  `BusyPointer'-prefs-ed  from the
NickPrefs package which is included in MagicWB).

    The busy pointer  `Bee.ilbm'  or its animation  `BeeAnim.pre' should
only be  used with  one of the   `...Yellow...'   pointers  or  with the
`ArrowLeftGrey.ilbm' or `ArrowRightGrey.ilbm' pointers,  because the bee
needs the color yellow.

    If you  want to use one of  the 8 color  pointers   (with the suffix
`8Col.ilbm'), you have to copy it directly to `ENVARC:sys' or `ENV:sys',
because the `Pointer'-prefs-ed only processes 4 color pointers. Example:
    
    Copy Prefs/Presets/ArrowLeftYellow8Col.ilbm ENVARC:sys/Pointer.ilbm

@EndNode

@Node "INSTALLATION" "ME_English/INSTALLATION"
@Next "RECHTLICHES"
@Prev "INHALT"
@Toc "Main"

Installation
~~~~~~~~~~~~
    Simply double-click the  InstallMagicExpansion  icon.   You need the
Commodore-Installer for ther installation,   but if you have got MUI you
have the Installer.
    Now you can  select what you  want to install and what not.   If you
don't know what to do, read the help texts.

    The script won't  install  any  icons,  because  I didn't know which
icons you want to use.   So you have to update the icons  `by hand' with
IconUpdate. Example:

    IconUpdate TCSWD MagicExpansion/Icons/Editor2 SC:c/se

    This line would update the icon of the SAS/C++ editor `se'. The tool
`IconUpdate'  was  written to  update  MagicWB icons.   So it  adds  the
tooltype
          
             »»»» Icon by Martin Huttenloher ««««  .

But don't get crazy because of this, the icon drawn by *ME*. :-)

@EndNode

